	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=9674971791723>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9674971791723>Kiting as bard IS possible</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9674971791723#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Aug 28th 5:12 PM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1117><span id= >Aolil</span></a><br><span id=notbold>4 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.40]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hmm... I am a bard and lvl26 at the moment and wanted to tell you my 2cp of thoughts..<br>1. bellow usually doesnt get resisted often even by low reds, as soon as mob is 5 or 6 lvls higher than you, you will see some resists..<br>2. neither lvl 2 area DoT nor the lvl 18 one has a good range, so you basically have to be in meelee range to use them what you certainly DON'T want<br>3. you dont need Jaxan's Jig<br>There are 2 good ways to kite with a bard IMHO:<br>a) (easy one) when you have sow on you, just choose a fine mob (white/yellow is good) get right into range and bellow it. Then you always just keep running backwards and use bellow again and again until the mob is dead.. you might have to take a turn, run around mob and start running backwards into the direction you came from... thanks to sow you are a bit faster than the mob so it wont get you and you can safely kill it with bellow<br>b) (hard one, without sow) first of all you have to find a mountain.. i did this at the one near sarnak fortress in Lake of ill omen. You have to pull a mob their and get up the mountain.. now you have to run down again and keep running circles up and down the hill... while you are doing it, you just bellow the mob.. why should one do this? well when PCs run down hills/mountains they are faster than NPCs. That way you get ahead from the monster and can get up to the top again while 1) staying in range for bellow 2) staying out of meelee range of mob<br><br>I should give you one more advice: whenever you are kiting a monster, press F9 three times before to switch you view mode and can see how far from you the mob is and you are warned of other inc mobs..<br><br>This is just what I experienced the last time. Hope you can use it well.<br><br>Aolil, master of 26 songs.<br>Member of Sentinels of Justice on the Tallon Zek server<br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
