	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>390 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.41]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>You said you were having some problems with out running your enemies?&nbsp;&nbsp;The trick i always used was to run in a large circle so that they would never get into melee range of me, but I could still hit them with my DD dong. BTW at level 12 bards become AMAZING at soloing becuase of this. After kiting something they can just go find another thing to kill, unlike druids who have to sit and med. It takes longer to kite as a bard, but you have no down time, so bards can acctually solo BETTER than druids. Also an answer to another one of your questions....can you jsut outrun and hide? Yes, that usually works well. Just be careful not to cause trains and to get REALLY far away from the thing...however thats usually not a problem since bards can run VERY fast.<br><br>Zuranthium/Corpusnuntia/Sunsong/Divineshadow/Naltec/Plantmaster/Naltec/Natalos<br><br>Player of many characters on the Nameless server.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
