	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I concur, in a party where you want to be low-taunt, Bellows is an excellent song to twist in.&nbsp;&nbsp;It will slowly add some fine damage (estimate about 50-80 per mob at level 20-25) on top of your buffs.  At the low to mid levels, you don't have a lot of choices for group buffs if you're going against melee mobs - anthem/chant, hymn, jig doesn't need to be in a twist, and you'll be saving the Rythms more for caster enemies.<br><br>Starting at level 25, you get your first party-wide damage shield which will be a better choice to twist in against most melee mobs.<br><br>In a high-taunt situation, yeah, toss Bellows out the friggin' window and pull out charm, mez, or chains.  I hear pixie strike is nice for that as well.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
