	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=96684516423337>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=96684516423337>Old Songs at high levels</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=96684516423337#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Aug 21st 4:06 AM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.30]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>For all the bards out there, never forget your old songs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Never.  My bard is lev 37 and for the past few levels I have grouped with 50+ chars (for camradrie) in Ocean of Tears killing Seafury Cyclops and the like.  It has got to the point where there is zero downtime, and a lot of that is thanks to older songs.<br><br>As an example, our usual team is a high level shaman, a high level warrior and myself.  I would normally just twist anthems and manasong in battle and this would keep both those guys happy.  When multiple pulls happened though, stamina took a caning so out pops the good old Jig o' Vigor :)  Yep, a level 3 song.  This would recharge the warrior so he would pull immediately.  Shaman was throwing 2 DoT's on and then canabalising his health to get mana back.  He was good to go 9 out of 10 times when the clops were dropping.<br><br>With the shamen buffs on us it was rare that we were injured, or needed healing.  Another example.  End of the night we would usually pop over and see if the oracle was up.  If he was the shamen and myself would act as a duo and get an oracle robe to either sell, or (usually) give to a fellow guild member.<br><br>The plan?  The shaman would kill the oracle after I lulled the guardian.  Yep, me, the LOWER member, would lull the 40ish level guardian.  With a level 8 song.  Would be levitated by the shammy and would slowly walk in across the water singing song every chance til I saw the message saying the guardian was sad.  then the shaman would pull the oracle and kill him.<br><br>Worked so effectively that we never took a hit, and I got the bonus of not getting any faction hits either :)  Was doing this at 34, and even then I was getting sucess from the song, with the guardian resisting and attacking only one time we tried this plan.<br><br>Point is, these are songs I got a year ago, yet they still have a viable use in the game.  As you level up and get higher, you WILL find that a lot of these songs make a good comeback - main reason is that they get so powerful that they challenge similar spells from other classes.<br><br>Remember our role - to fill gaps and reduce downtime.  We do this better than any other class and will usually get a group position simply for this reason.  Most of our songs dont get old, just better.<br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
