	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9668398882932>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=9668398882932>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9668398882932>Songs Vs Weapons for the solo bard in the High teens/Low 20'</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=9668398882932#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Aug 21st 2:38 AM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>A lot of bards don't realise, I certainly didn't with my first wee bard, that your weapons become redundant in most situations at level 18 when in the world on your own (ie not grouped).&nbsp;&nbsp;Thats right, absolutely redundant!  I am currently the 23rd level proud owner of a Bladed thulian claw and dragoon dirk - that exist just to live in my backpack!  <br><br>What should you be doing?.... why twisting with instruments of course!  You have denons disruptive discord (brass), hymn of restoration (string), and chords of dissonance (strings).  Use them!!!!!  <br><br>Firstly make a new hotkey sheet.<br>Hotkey all three songs in slots 1-3, your offhand slot (slot 5), and your favourite combination of either selos/bellow/a inventory slot.  I go for an inventory slot (slot 6) and bellow (slot 4) personally.<br><br>Now go somewhere where you can safely practise on eaay blues or tough green npcs... wisps or crocs are good at 18 to practise on.<br><br>Now, have the right hotsheet up, your brass instrument in your offhand slot, your string instrument on your mouse cursor, and start up Denons by pressing 1.  When you see the targeted NPC wince, start hymn up.  Now put your string instrument into your offhand slot.  When it the song takes effect, start chords.  No need to change instruments here as discord is a string song as well.  When the NPC winces.... start denons, switch instruments.... rise and repeat till no more bad guy :) .  Oh and don't forget to punch the bugga!<br><br>Points to note!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!<br><br>It is only important to have the correct instrument in place when the songs effect goes off, not when you start the song.  Thats why you start a song then put the instrument in place.<br><br>As with other twisting guides you can actually stop a song and start another one a second or so (depending on your internet connection) before the effect starts.  My ping-time ain't all that consistant but I still switch songs after about 3 seconds regardless.... still works.<br><br>Generally (well.... definitely) it is safest to use this method in non crowded area.  Pull your victim to a zone wall, etc.  The songs are Area Effect so you would otherwise draw a bit more of a crowd than you were looking to.<br><br>Don't use this method on multible pulls in groups - your don't want to start doing silly things like breaking an enchanters mez, pulling two mobs onto yourself that don't appreciate your mucis and quickly quiet you up, etc, ................ and 99% of the time in groups a bard is better suited doing something other than trying to be the main damage dealer anyway.  <br><br>Oh and if you haven't got your brass skill up, you'll find starting denons up impossible!  Go to a safe place (arena or the cave in east commons (not tunnel), put your brass instrument in your off hand slot, and get it started after the 20 trys it will take you.  Now walk away from your PC.  It will take hours to get your brass skill up to go and watch tv... or better yet, get exercise!  I did this overnight myself.....<br><br>Try to use this method on a tough blue or two weak blues at once.  You'll find you can deal more damage than wwith your weapons and have less downtime (err... not that we have much) at the end of a fight.<br><br>Oh, if you are getting bashed repeatedly, prioritise having denons and heal going.  Better yet fight npcs that don't bash, they are little bastards!<br><br>Okay, RAMBLED on enough.... sure you can figure out the rest!!!!<br><br>Ayre of Terris.<br>The wee surfer bard. <br><br><br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
