	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96660800817223>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=96660800817223>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=96660800817223>True Barding begins</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=96660800817223#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 10:13 AM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=374><span id=Sage>Sapper</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>26 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.63]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>After level 5, you simply must group.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is possible for us to solo, but Bards are truly "Party Animals".  Around Qeynos, You have 4 options from 5-10.  Black Burrow, Qeynos Hills, West Karanas, and Qeynos Aquaducts.<br>Black Burrow:  I never much liked this dungeon.  Cant really say why, just way to many trains I guess.  I dont mind trains now, I practically LIVE in Mistmoore now (L25), but the trains in BB were just too many.  Excpect at least a train every 10 minutes in primetime.  Good EXP, and turn in the Gnoll teeth to Cpt Tillen, in the Warriors guild (by the arena) in Qeynos.  He gives you a moonstone, wich you turn in to the guy behind the bar in that bar Trumpy hangs out at (The quest is listed here in great detail).<br>Qeynos Hills:  Nice psot to hunt, has alittle of everything, Bears & Wolves for tailoring and maybe the Miller Bear and Wolf clothing quests.  Skeletons near the Ruins (watch for Varsoom though), and Gnolls all over.  Plus, one or twice a month, Q Hills gets invaded by Undead, and you can get in a group and rake in the exp and loot in the GM events.<br>West Karanas:  HUGE zone.  Group up and kill bears and lions, stay close to the Guard towers and STAY AWAY FROM THE BANDIT CAMPS.  Con all NPCs, there is a farm just north of the road by teh second tower (T2) that spawns some nasty evil farmers and bandits.  later on you will slaughter them in the bucketloads, but stay clear of them for now.  This is the time when you will learn how much Bards are appreciated.  Your ATK Speed, Dex, and Str buff, Heal, and Run songs are loved by all, and your Corspe locate song WILL be used a lot (WK is a big zone).  Now is when you will expereinece a dilemma as well.  You will be with your group, and someone will shout for help with a corspe locate.  What you do is your decision, but your first loyalty is with your group.  I always got my groups OK before I took off to help someone out.<br>Qeynos Aquaducts/Catacombs:  You can actually start here a little earlier, as there are plenty of greens wandering about.  The bast place to enter (for me at least) at the ivy coverd spot left of the main gate.  Walk through the wall (its an illusion) and dive in the well.  Its scary the first time!  make sure you have a lightstone or Fire beetle eye, so you can see underwater.  There are maps here of the aquaducts, but to get to the smuggler and thug camps, hug the left wall untill you come to a pool room.  walk through the illusionary wall at the end, and you are in the lower level.  Thugs will be tough unless you are in a  strong group, but Smugglers should be OK.  If you ever walk through a wall and see the walls coeverd with red, turn around and walk out.  You have stumbled into the Evil temple of Bertox, and will be killed quickly.  Also, if you see a Zombie named Drosco walking around, kill him and loot his Amulet of Thunder, its a nice stat boost for a young Bard.<br>If you ever find yourself in a large group that is tank heavy, equip a Peirce or 1HB weapon.  Train in them now.  Alter on, you will get Dual wield, and have some great stats boosting and proc'ing weapons to use, dont be stuck with a great weapon that you cant use later on.  Train now to avoid the pain later.<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Sapper Diesalot, At Deaths Door.&nbsp;&nbsp;"Chuck Berry cant twist this good!"</td></td></tr>
